From the same owner of Wicker Park‚Äôs Amaru, Bloom employs a dramatically radical perspective on vegan cooking: don‚Äôt be boring. I mentioned it previously in my write up for Mag Mile‚Äôs Althea, but I‚Äôve found a lot of vegan cooking over-dwells on recreating meat flavors with plants. Bloom excels at carving its own path with dishes that aren‚Äôt always defined by substituting meat. A solid example for me is the potato tostones, which at its core is just a plate of damn good potatoes. It‚Äôs also a great indication of the global outlook, with spins on curry, gnocchi, and ceviche. A healthy and refined escapism for anyone who‚Äôs feeling a bit of meat-guilt or just wants to see changes in their diet, Bloom is blossoming in Wicker Park.
